meta {
  name: GET tripstatistics shortTerm (#24 closer)
  type: http
  seq: 4
}

get {
  url: {{base_url}}/vehicle/v1/vehicles/{{vin}}/tripstatistics?type=shortTerm
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v1.14.0 (#24 Verbrauchsdaten / Trip Stats) — VW EU + Audi.

  Returns {tripDataList: {tripData: [...]}}. Sort by overallMileage
  desc, take [0] = most recent trip. Consumption fields come back as
  integers ×10 (averageFuelConsumption: 68 = 6.8 l/100km).

  4 sensors fed: last_trip_distance_km, _avg_speed_kmh,
  _avg_fuel_consumption_l_100km, _avg_electric_consumption_kwh_100km
  + recent_trips as extra_state_attributes.

  Implementation: VWEUClient.get_trip_statistics() +
  coordinator._parse_trip_statistics + refresh_trip_statistics
  (1h cache, brand-restricted to audi+volkswagen).
}
